The reader may safely be trusted to decide whether Hussitism is or is not mere Wycliffianism, imported into Bo· hemia. That the so·called ‘Pte-Hussite’ reformers knew nothing of these doctrineS, and had nothing to do with a teaching which - as the above quotations prove —dealt a deadly blow to the existing order of the Church, is obvious. But this teaching forms the root, the cornerstone of the Hussitc system, which evolved itself more gently in one party, more sternly in the other - that of the Taborites — but always on Wycliffian lines.
